text:
East 151st Street (foreground), at the N.E. corner of Exterior Street, showing a general view in a northeasterly direction. In the center background is visible the lower end of Franz Siegel Park and, to its left, the Bronx County Court House.

May 6, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

Grand Concourse (left), south from near E. 156th Street, as seen from the lower end of Franz Siegel Park. In the left background are discernible the Hell Gate and Triborough Bridges.

View 2: June 9, 1940

P. L. Sperr

text:
Franz Sigel Park: A view north from about East 156th Street. In the background appears the Bronx County Court House, on the north side of East 158th Street.

April 30, 1937.
